50 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
51 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
52 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
53 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
54 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
55 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
56  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
57 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
58 #else
59 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
60 #endif
61 #endif
62 
63 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
64 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
65 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
66 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
67 #else
68 #error "unknown compiler"
69 #endif
70 
71 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
72 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
73 #else
74 #include <cstdio>
75 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
76  do { \
77  fputs(msg, stderr); \
78  DNNL_TRAP(); \
79  } while (0)
80 #endif

96 struct error : public std::exception {
97  dnnl_status_t status;
98  const char *message;
99 
104  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
105  : status(status), message(message) {}
106 
108  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
109 
115  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
116  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
117  }
118 };
119 
121 template <typename T>
122 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
123  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
124  const int size = (int)v.size();
125  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
126  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
127 }

131 template <typename T>
132 struct handle_traits {};
133 
147 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
148 struct handle {
149 private:
150  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
151  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
152 
153 protected:
154  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
155  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
156 
157 public:
165  handle() = default;
166 
168  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
170  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
172  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
174  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
175 
181  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
182 
188  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
189  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
190  }
191 
197  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
198  T result = data_.get();
199  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
200  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
201  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
202  return result;
203  }
204 
209  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
210 
214  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
215 
222  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
223  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
224  }
225 
232  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
233 };

401 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
402  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
403  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
404  // returns a C type.
405  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
406  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
407  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
408  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
409  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
410 }

666 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
667  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
668  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
669  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
670  } \
671 \
672  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
673  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
674  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
675  } \
676 \
677  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
678  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
679  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
680  } \
681 \
682  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
683  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
684  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
685  return lhs; \
686  } \
687 \
688  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
689  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
690  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
691  return lhs; \
692  } \
693 \
694  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
695  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
696  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
697  return lhs; \
698  } \
699 \
700  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
701  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
702  }
703 
704 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
705 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

900  "could not create an engine");

938  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),

1049  stream_attr(engine::kind kind) {
1050  dnnl_stream_attr_t attr;
1051  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_create(&attr, convert_to_c(kind)),
1052  "could not create stream attributes");
1053  reset(attr);
1054  }
1055 
1056 #if DNNL_CPU_THREADING_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_THREADPOOL
1057  void set_threadpool(threadpool_iface *threadpool) {
1065  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_set_threadpool(get(), threadpool),
1066  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1067  }
1068 
1074  threadpool_iface *get_threadpool() {
1075  threadpool_iface *tp;
1076  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_get_threadpool(get(), (void **)&tp),
1077  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1078  return tp;
1079  }
1080 #endif
1081 };
1082 
1084 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1085  using handle::handle;
1086 
1088  enum class flags : unsigned {
1091  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1093  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1095  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1097  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1098  };
1099 
1102  stream() = default;
1103 
1110  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags,
1111  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1112  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1113  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, engine.get(),
1114  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags),
1115  attr.get(true)),
1116  "could not create a stream");
1117  reset(stream);
1118  }
1119 
1120 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1121  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1126  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1127  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1128  "could not create a stream");
1129  reset(stream);
1130  }
1131 
1134  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1135  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1136  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1137  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1138  return queue;
1139  }
1140 #endif
1141 
1142 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1143  DNNL_API stream(const engine &aengine, cl::sycl::queue &queue);
1148 
1151  cl::sycl::queue DNNL_API get_sycl_queue() const;
1152 #endif
1153 
1156  stream &wait() {
1157  error::wrap_c_api(
1158  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1159  return *this;
1160  }
1161 };

1807  struct desc {
1808  friend struct memory;
1810  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1811 
1814  desc() : data() {}
1815 
1831  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1832  format_tag format_tag, bool allow_empty = false)
1833  : data() {
1834  validate_dims(dims);
1835  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1836  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1837  convert_to_c(format_tag));
1838  if (!allow_empty)
1839  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1840  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1841  "format tag");
1842  }
1843 
1859  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1860  const memory::dims &strides, bool allow_empty = false)
1861  : data() {
1862  validate_dims(dims);
1863  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)dims.size());
1864  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1865  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1866  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1867  if (!allow_empty)
1868  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1869  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1870  "strides");
1871  }
1872 
1876  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1877 
1880  //
1889  desc submemory_desc(const memory::dims &dims,
1890  const memory::dims &offsets, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1891  validate_dims(dims, data.ndims);
1892  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1893  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1894  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1895  &sub_md, &data, dims.data(), offsets.data());
1896  if (!allow_empty)
1897  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1898  return desc(sub_md);
1899  }
1900 
1945  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1946  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(dims, 1);
1947  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1948  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1949  &out_md, &data, (int)dims.size(), dims.data());
1950  if (!allow_empty)
1951  error::wrap_c_api(
1952  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1953  return desc(out_md);
1954  }
1955 
1992  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1993  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1994  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
1995  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1996  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
1997  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
1998  if (!allow_empty)
1999  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2000  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
2001  return desc(out_md);
2002  }
2003 
2008  memory::dims dims() const {
2009  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
2010  }
2011 
2014  memory::data_type data_type() const {
2015  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
2016  }
2017 
2022  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
2023 
2027  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
2028 
2033  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
2034  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
2035  }
2036 
2041  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2042  };

2258 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL && defined(DNNL_USE_SYCL_BUFFERS)
2259  template <typename T, int ndims = 1>
2266  cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> get_sycl_buffer(size_t *offset = nullptr) const {
2267  static_assert(ndims == 1, "only 1D buffers supported");
2268 
2269  void *handle_ptr;
2270  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_data_handle(get(), &handle_ptr),
2271  "could not get SYCL buffer object");
2272 
2273  // XXX: workaround for ComputeCpp
2274  // ComputeCpp fails to construct zero-range buffer
2275  if (!handle_ptr)
2276  return cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims>(cl::sycl::range<1>(1));
2277 
2278  auto &buf_u8 = *static_cast<cl::sycl::buffer<uint8_t, 1> *>(handle_ptr);
2279  if (offset) *offset = 0;
2280  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf_u8.get_size() / sizeof(T));
2281  return buf_u8.reinterpret<T, 1>(range);
2282  }
2283 
2289  template <typename T, int ndims>
2290  void set_sycl_buffer(cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> &buf) {
2291  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf.get_size());
2292  auto buf_u8 = buf.template reinterpret<uint8_t, 1>(range);
2293  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_set_data_handle(
2294  get(), static_cast<void *>(&buf_u8)),
2295  "could not set SYCL buffer object");
2296  }
2297 #endif

3000  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
3001  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
3002  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
3003  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
3004  query::exec_arg_md};
3005  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
3006  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
3007  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3008  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
3009 
3010  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
3011  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
3012  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
3013  }

3139  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
3140  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_c_attr;
3141  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_c_attr),
3142  "could not get attributes from a primitive descriptor");
3143  dnnl_primitive_attr_t c_attr;

3151  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
3152  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
3153  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
3154  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3155  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3156  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
3157  }
3158 
3159 protected:
3163  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3164  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3165  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3166  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3167  reset(new_pd);
3168  }
3169 
3183  primitive_desc_base(
3184  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3185  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3186 
3198  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3199  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
3200  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
3201 
3215  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3216  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3217  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3218  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3219  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3220 
3221  dnnl_status_t rc;
3222 
3223  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3224  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3225  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3226 
3227  // Check that primitive kind matches
3228  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3229  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3230  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3231  error::wrap_c_api(
3232  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3233  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3234  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3235  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3236 
3237  // Check that propagation kind matches
3238  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3239  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3240  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3241 
3242  // Something went wrong
3243  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3244  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3245  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3246  "descriptor");
3247 
3248  // Everything is fine
3249  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3250  || (rc == dnnl_success
3251  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3252  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3253  reset_with_clone(pd);
3254  return;
3255  }
3256 
3257  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3258  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3259  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3260  }
3261 
3262  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3263 };

3425 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3426  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3427  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;

3431  return c_mems;

3640 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3641  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3642 
3643  primitive_desc() = default;
3644 
3667  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3668  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3669  bool allow_empty = false)
3670  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3671  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3672  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3673  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3674  if (!allow_empty)
3675  error::wrap_c_api(
3676  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3677  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3678  fetch_impl();
3679  }
3680 
3685  bool next_impl() {
3686  dnnl_status_t status
3687  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3688  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3689  error::wrap_c_api(
3690  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3691  fetch_impl();
3692  return true;
3693  }
3694 
3695 private:
3696  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3697  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3698  void fetch_impl() {
3699  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3700  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3701  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3702  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3703  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3704  "descriptor iterator");
3705  reset(pd);
3706  }
3707 };

3765  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,

3875  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
3876  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &weights_desc,

3878  const memory::dims &strides, const memory::dims &dilates,

5139  memory::validate_dims(dilates, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5140  memory::validate_dims(padding_l, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5141  memory::validate_dims(padding_r, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5142  error::wrap_c_api(
5143  dnnl_dilated_deconvolution_backward_weights_desc_init(&data,
5144  convert_to_c(algorithm), &src_desc.data,
5145  &diff_weights_desc.data, &diff_bias_desc.data,
5146  &diff_dst_desc.data, &strides[0], &dilates[0],
5147  &padding_l[0], &padding_r[0]),
5148  "could not create a descriptor for a dilated deconvolution "
5149  "weights gradient primitive");
5150  }
5151 
5185  desc(algorithm algorithm, const memory::desc &src_desc,
5186  const memory::desc &diff_weights_desc,
5187  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc, const memory::dims &strides,
5188  const memory::dims &dilates, const memory::dims &padding_l,
5189  const memory::dims &padding_r) {
5190  memory::validate_dims(strides, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5191  memory::validate_dims(dilates, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5192  memory::validate_dims(padding_l, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5193  memory::validate_dims(padding_r, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
5194  error::wrap_c_api(
5195  dnnl_dilated_deconvolution_backward_weights_desc_init(&data,
5196  convert_to_c(algorithm), &src_desc.data,
5197  &diff_weights_desc.data, nullptr,
5198  &diff_dst_desc.data, &strides[0], &dilates[0],
5199  &padding_l[0], &padding_r[0]),
5200  "could not create a descriptor for a dilated deconvolution "
5201  "weights gradient primitive");
5202  }
5203  };

7754  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7755  //
7756  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7757  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7758  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7759  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7760  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7761  //
7762  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7763  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7764  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7765  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7766  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7767  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7768  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7769  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7770  dnnl_status_t rc;
7771  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7772  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7773  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7774  "for an RNN primitive");
7775 
7776  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7777  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7778  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7779 
7780  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7781  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7782  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7783  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7784 
7785  if (!ok)
7786  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7787  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7788  "RNN primitive");
7789 
7790  reset_with_clone(pd);
7791  }
7792 };
7793

7799 
7856  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm activation, rnn_direction direction,
7857  const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
7858  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,
7859  const memory::desc &weights_layer_desc,
7860  const memory::desc &weights_iter_desc,
7861  const memory::desc &bias_desc,
7862  const memory::desc &dst_layer_desc,
7863  const memory::desc &dst_iter_desc,
7864  rnn_flags flags = rnn_flags::undef, float alpha = 0.0f,
7865  float beta = 0.0f) {
7866  error::wrap_c_api(
7867  dnnl_vanilla_rnn_forward_desc_init(&data,
7868  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
7869  dnnl::convert_to_c(activation),
7870  dnnl::convert_to_c(direction), &src_layer_desc.data,
7871  &src_iter_desc.data, &weights_layer_desc.data,
7872  &weights_iter_desc.data, &bias_desc.data,
7873  &dst_layer_desc.data, &dst_iter_desc.data,
7874  dnnl::convert_to_c(flags), alpha, beta),
7875  "could not create a descriptor for a vanilla RNN forward "
7876  "propagation primitive");
7877  }
7878  };

10467 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
10469  struct desc {
10470  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
10471 
10493  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10494  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10495  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10496  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10497  convert_to_c(algorithm), nullptr,
10498  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10499  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10500  }
10501 
10516  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10517  const std::vector<float> &factors,
10518  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
10519  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10520  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10521  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10522  convert_to_c(algorithm), &factors[0],
10523  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
10524  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10525  }
10526 
10549  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10550  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
10551  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10552  if (!factors.empty())
10553  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10554  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10555  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10556  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10557  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10558  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10559  }
10560  };

10934 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &stream,
10935  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10936  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10937  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10938  for (const auto &a : args)
10939  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10940 
10941  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
10942  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10943  "could not execute a primitive");
10944 }
